flowRoot.flowPara: Quite simply, yes.
Brexit won’t be finalised until 29th March 2019. At any point up to then, we can change our
minds and stay in the EU.

The legal process to stop Brexit is simple. Theresa May started the leaving process by notifying the commission of our intention to leave, in accordance with Article 50 of the Treaty of Lisbon. To stop the process we simply have to write to the commission withdrawing that notification.

You may have heard people say that the legal position on the withdrawal of notification is unclear. In strict legal terms this is true — it has never been tested. However, the issue is more political than legal: if the 27 accept us cancelling Brexit, the legal situation is not important.

text.tspan: Can the British people stop Brexit?

flowRoot.flowPara: e have confirmation from many of those on the EU side of the negotiations that they would be delighted for us to remain in the EU:
"Some of my British friends have even asked me whether Brexit could be reversed, and whether I could imagine an outcome where the UK stays part of the EU.
"I told them that in fact the European Union was built on dreams that seemed impossible to achieve. So, who knows?"
– Donald Tusk, President of European Council
“President Tusk also made some comments on Brexit, he said that our door remains open. I hope that will be heard clearly in London”
– Jean-Claude Juncker, President of the
European Commission
“The door remains open for the UK to stay in the European Union”
– Ireland’s Taoiseach, Leo Varadkar
"Britain could still cancel Brexit and stay in the European Union on the same terms it currently enjoys"
– Nathalie Loiseau, French government’s
European affairs minister
"It is purely a responsibility of the UK that they have to make up their mind if they want to change their decision"
– Guy Verhofstadt, EU Parliament's lead
negotiator for Brexit
"Germany would not stand in the way of the UK returning to the Union. If they wanted to change their decision, of course, they would find open doors"
– Wolfgang Schaeuble, German Finance Minister
